🟢 EASY (1–30)
1. Two Sum
Dado um array nums e um inteiro target, retorne os índices de dois números cuja soma seja igual a target.

2. Contains Duplicate
Dado um array de inteiros, retorne true se existir algum elemento duplicado.

3. Valid Anagram
Dadas duas strings s e t, retorne true se t for um anagrama de s.

4. Move Zeroes
Mova todos os zeros para o final do array mantendo a ordem relativa.

5. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
Given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a stock on day i,
return the maximum profit you can achieve from a single buy and a single sell.
You must buy before you sell.
If no profit is possible, return 0.

6. Valid Parentheses
Given a string containing only the characters ()[]{},
return true if the input string is valid.
A string is valid if:
Open brackets are closed by the same type.
Open brackets are closed in the correct order.
Every closing bracket has a matching open bracket.

7. Majority Element
Implement a function that returns the n-th Fibonacci number.
Assume the classic definition:
F(0) = 0
F(1) = 1
F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2)

8. Missing Number
Given an array nums containing n distinct numbers in the range [0, n],
return the only number in the range that is missing from the array.

9. Reverse String
Write a function that reverses a string in-place.
The input is given as a character array.

10. Merge Two Sorted Arrays
You are given two sorted integer arrays nums1 and nums2,
and two integers m and n.
Merge nums2 into nums1 as one sorted array.
nums1 has a size of m + n,
where the last n elements are zeros and should be ignored.

11. Intersection of Two Arrays
Given two integer arrays nums1 and nums2,
return an array of their intersection.
Each element in the result must be unique,
and the result can be returned in any order.

12. Happy Number
Write an algorithm to determine if a number n is a happy number.
A happy number is defined as:
Starting with any positive integer,
Replace the number by the sum of the squares of its digits.
Repeat the process until:
The number equals 1 → happy
Or it loops endlessly → not happy

13. First Unique Character
Given a string s, return the index of the first non-repeating character.
If it does not exist, return -1.

14. Climbing Stairs
You are climbing a staircase with n steps.
Each time you can climb 1 or 2 steps.
Return the number of distinct ways to reach the top.

15. Fibonacci
Implemente Fibonacci (iterativo e recursivo).

16. Maximum Depth of Binary Tree
Given the root of a binary tree, return its maximum depth.
Maximum depth = number of nodes in the longest path from the root node to the farthest.

17. Symmetric Tree
Given the root of a binary tree, check whether it is a mirror of itself (symmetric around its center).

18. Invert Binary Tree
Given the root of a binary tree, invert the tree (mirror it).

19. Implement Stack using Queue
Implemente stack usando apenas queue.

20. Implement Queue using Stack
Implemente queue usando apenas stack.

21. Palindrome Number
Given an integer x, return true if x is a palindrome, and false otherwise.

22. Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array
Given a sorted array nums, remove the duplicates in-place such that each element appears only once and return the new length.
Do not allocate extra space for another array.
Modify the input array in-place.

23. Plus One
You are given a large integer represented as an array of digits.
Increment the integer by one and return the resulting array.

24. Valid Palindrome
Given a string s, determine if it is a palindrome, considering only alphanumeric characters and ignoring cases.

25. Two Sum II (array ordenado)
Given a 1-indexed sorted array numbers,
find two numbers such that they add up to a specific target.

26. Find Pivot Index
Given an integer array nums, return the pivot index.

27. Reverse Linked List
Given the head of a singly linked list, reverse the list and return its new head.

28. Detect Cycle in Linked List
Given the head of a linked list, determine if the list has a cycle in it.

29. Balanced Binary Tree
Verifique se árvore é balanceada.
30. Count Primes
Conte quantos números primos existem até n.

